ttl.description: Required. Specifies the "time-to-live" for the set of playable locations. You can use this value to determine how long to cache the set of playable locations. After this length of time, your back-end game server should issue a new SamplePlayableLocations request to get a fresh set of playable locations (because for example, they might have been removed, a park might have closed for the day, a business might have closed permanently).
